<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Would mix HC and LS be a problem?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17367&amp;p=218855#p218855"><![CDATA[
Er.... not really? M2 could be used as a DRAM refresh clock, but it would only hold its value while it's running. When reset is held, the clock stops, and the contents of the single bit of DRAM will be lost.<br /><br />The circuit you linked to is an S-R latch, not a JK register. On its own, it can't do a useful thing in response to a clock input, so the reset-detection circuit isn't related.<br /><br />Regardless, it's still so many passives that I can't imagine it's cheaper than something more nearly integrated.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Mon May 21, 2018 2:33 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
